The paper focuses on computationally modeling actors and evaluating narrative content, which suggests a natural fit with the arXiv sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of Gaussian embeddings and machine learning techniques also suggests a potential fit with Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of persona topics and descriptive keywords suggests a potential fit with Information Retrieval (cs.IR), while the use of movie genres and character roles suggests a potential fit with Computer Vision (cs.CV).
